.\" -*- mode: nroff; -*-
.Dd August 24, 2025
.Dt NOCT 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm noct
.Nd Noct programming language CLI
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar file
.br
.Nm
.Fl Fl compile
.Ar files ...
.br
.Nm
.Fl Fl ansic
.Ar out.c
.Ar in files ...
.br
.Nm
.Fl Fl elisp
.Ar out.el
.Ar in files ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
command is the command-line interface for the Noct programming language.
It can directly run a program, run REPL, compile sources into Noct bytecode,
or transpile sources to ANSI C or Emacs Lisp.
.Pp
If no arguments are provided, runs the REPL.
.Pp
If no option is given and a
.Ar file
is provided,
.Nm
executes the program.
.Sh OPTIONS
The following options are supported:
.Bl -tag -width 14n
.It Fl Fl compile
Compile one or more input source files into Noct bytecode files.
.It Fl Fl ansic Ar out.c Ar in files ...
Transpile the specified input source files into a single ANSI C source file
.Ar out.c .
The generated C file can be compiled with the Noct runtime.
.It Fl Fl elisp Ar out.el Ar in files ...
Transpile the specified input source files into a single Emacs Lisp file
.Ar out.el .
The resulting file can be loaded into Emacs to run the program using
Noct's Emacs integration (if available).
.El
.Sh OPERANDS
.Bl -tag -width 14n
.It Ar file
Path to a Noct source file to execute.
When present without other options,
.Nm
runs the program.
.It Ar files
One or more input source files.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Nm
exits 0 on success and >0 if an error occurs (syntax error, I/O failure,
code generation error, or runtime failure).
.Sh EXAMPLES
Run REPL:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ noct
.Ed
.Pp
Run a program:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ noct hello.noct
.Ed
.Pp
Compile multiple sources to bytecode:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ noct --compile lib.noct main.noct
.Ed
.Pp
Transpile to ANSI C:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ noct --ansic aot_source.c main.noct lib.noct
.Ed
.Pp
Generate a single Emacs Lisp file:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ noct --elisp app.el main.noct lib.noct
.Ed
